GeneralExplanation.Identifier: ORGANIZATION'S PROCESS USED TO REVIEW FORM 990
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE BOARD REVIEWS A DRAFT COPY OF THE TAX RETURN FOR ACCURACY AND COMPLETENESS PRIOR TO SIGNING AND FILING THE TAX RETURN.
CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY FORM IS DISTRIBUTED PERIODICALLY THROUGHOUT THE YEAR AND PARTICIPANTS ACKNOWLEDGE THAT THERE IS NO CONFLICT OF INTEREST DUE TO THEIR ASSOCIATION.

THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD REVIEWS THE ANNUAL SALARY SURVEY PREPARED BY FEEDING AMERICA, A NATIONAL NONPROFIT DISTRIBUTOR OF DONATED PRODUCE IN THE FOOD BANK NETWORK, AND PREPARES WRITTEN DOCUMENTATION OF THE REVIEW PROCESS AND SALARY RECOMMENDATION. THE BOARD THEN APPROVES THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR'S SALARY.
THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
